Exceptions. No set-off or counterclaim shall be allowed in favor of any person where:
The obligation of the insurer to the person would not at the date of the filing of a petition for liquidation entitle him to share as a claimant in the assets of the insurer;
The obligation of the insurer to the person was purchased by or transferred to the person with a view to its being used as a set-off;
The obligation of the person is to pay an assessment levied against the members or subscribers of the insurer, or is to pay a balance upon a subscription to the capital stock of the insurer, or is in any other way in the nature of a capital contribution; or
The obligation of the person is to pay earned premiums to the insurer. However, the provisions of this paragraph shall only apply to reinsurance contracts entered into prior to July 13, 2004.
